# Oral_cancer .gitignore
# Principle: commit SOURCE (originals + code + the markdown findings).
# Never commit GENERATED output (docs say it is safe to delete and rebuild).
# NOTE: git .gitignore has NO inline comments — every comment is its own line.

# --- Generated / regenerable: never commit ---
artifacts/
runs/
data/new_data/
Experimenting/_datasets/

# Ultralytics training/val dumps (plots, args, checkpoints). The findings
# (metrics.{json,txt}, run.json, metrics_*_negatives.*) sit ABOVE these and
# are kept on purpose.
Experimenting/results/*/train/
Experimenting/results/*/val/

# Ultralytics label cache
*.cache

# --- Model weights: large and regenerable ---
# Ignoring these means a fresh clone must RETRAIN before
# eval_fair_negatives.py / eval_match_rules.py / Number A will run.
# To ship a specific one anyway: git add -f path/to/best.pt
*.pt

# --- Python / tooling noise ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.DS_Store
.venv/
.env
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- Decide yourself (tracked by default; uncomment a line to exclude) ---
# data/additional/  : 201M Roboflow third-party; only exp7/convert need it.
# data/additional/
# data/Normal/       : 120M patient phone photos; see privacy note before any public push.
